y&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080"},{"id":"jura","name":"Jura","nameIt":"Jura","capital":"Delémont","lat":47.35,"lng":7.34,"emoji":"🥾","colour":"ff2196f3","boundingBox":{"north":47.55,"south":47.1,"east":7.7,"west":6.95},"placeCount":7,"restaurantCount":14,"bestTimeToVisit":"Spring and autumn are perfect for hiking through this scenic region of limestone ridges and charming small towns.","heroImage":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1563307057-0107aaaef253?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxBcmJvaXMlMjB3aW5lJTIwdG93biUyMEp1cmF8ZW58MXwwfHx8MTc4MzQ1ODI4OHww&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Maryline Waldy"},"cardImage":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1563307057-0107aaaef253?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxBcmJvaXMlMjB3aW5lJTIwdG93biUyMEp1cmF8ZW58MXwwfHx8MTc4MzQ1ODI4OHww&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080"},{"id":"neuchatel","name":"Neuchâtel","nameIt":"Neuchâtel","capital":"Neuchâtel","lat":46.99,"lng":6.93,"emoji":"🕰️","colour":"ffff9800","boundingBox":{"north":47.35,"south":46.65,"east":7.3,"west":6.55},"placeCount":4,"restaurantCount":14,"bestTimeToVisit":"Visit in spring or autumn to enjoy this elegant lakeside city with pleasant weather and wine-growing landscapes.","heroImage":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1743836447602-3a1d69379f2b?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxOZXVjaCVDMyVBMnRlbCUyMG9sZCUyMHRvd24lMjBjYXN0bGV8ZW58MXwwfHx8MTc4MzQ1ODM0M3ww&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"William Ducret"},"cardImage":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1743836447602-3a1d69379f2b?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxOZXVjaCVDMyVBMnRlbCUyMG9sZCUyMHRvd24lMjBjYXN0bGV8ZW58MXwwfHx8MTc4MzQ1ODM0M3ww&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080"},{"id":"fribourg","name":"Fribourg","nameIt":"Fribourg","capital":"Fribourg","lat":46.8,"lng":7.16,"emoji":"🏛️","colour":"ff9c27b0","boundingBox":{"north":47.15,"south":46.45,"east":7.7,"west":6.6},"placeCount":5,"restaurantCount":15,"bestTimeToVisit":"Spring and autumn provide pleasant weather for exploring medieval towns and rolling countryside between Swiss culture regions.","heroImage":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1578145633942-2a45950d5d45?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxSb21vbnQlMjBTd2l0emVybGFuZCUyMHRvd24lMjBjYXN0bGV8ZW58MXwwfHx8MTc4MzQ1ODM5Mnww&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Uwe Conrad"},"cardImage":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1578145633942-2a45950d5d45?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxSb21vbnQlMjBTd2l0emVybGFuZCUyMHRvd24lMjBjYXN0bGV8ZW58MXwwfHx8MTc4MzQ1ODM5Mnww&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080"}],"top10":[{"rank":1,"name":"Zurich Old Town","placeId":"zurich_city","regionId":"zurich","regionName":"Zurich","image":null,"description":"The historic heart of Zurich featuring narrow cobblestone streets, medieval guild houses, and charming squares like Münsterhof and St. Petersplatz. This atmospheric district is perfect for wandering, shopping, dining, and experiencing authentic Swiss heritage."},{"rank":2,"name":"Lucerne","placeId":"lucerne_city","regionId":"lucerne","regionName":"Lucerne","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1606245387731-f94ca65a7577?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxMdWNlcm5lJTIwQ2hhcGVsJTIwQnJpZGdlJTIwc3Vuc2V0fGVufDF8MHx8fDE3ODM0NTA4OTB8MA&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"joel protasio"},"description":"Switzerland's most picturesque lakeside city, famous for its well-preserved medieval old town, charming bridges, and stunning Alpine backdrop. The city is the cultural and tourism heart of central Switzerland with excellent museums, restaurants, and water activities on Lake Lucerne."},{"rank":3,"name":"Interlaken","placeId":"interlaken","regionId":"valais","regionName":"Valais","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1578569516094-33063f8acb44?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxJbnRlcmxha2VuJTIwSnVuZ2ZyYXUlMjB2aWV3fGVufDF8MHx8fDE3ODM0NDQwNDF8MA&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Josef Ivan Jimenea"},"description":"Nestled between lakes Thun and Brienz with stunning views of the Eiger, Jungfrau, and Matterhorn, Interlaken is the adventure capital of Switzerland offering hiking, paragliding, and access to the Jungfrau region. Its position as a gateway to the Bernese Oberland makes it essential for any Swiss Alps itinerary."},{"rank":4,"name":"Geneva","placeId":"geneva_city","regionId":"geneva","regionName":"Geneva","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1574904935745-7e40279f589d?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxHZW5ldmElMjBTd2l0emVybGFuZHxlbnwxfDB8fHwxNzg0MDI2NjY2fDA&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"visualsoflukas"},"description":"Home to the United Nations and numerous international organizations, Geneva blends cosmopolitan sophistication with lakeside elegance on Lake Geneva. Visitors are drawn to its museums, the iconic Jet d'Eau fountain, and its role as a global diplomatic center."},{"rank":5,"name":"Jungfrau","placeId":"jungfrau_region","regionId":"bern","regionName":"Bern","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1597216394928-e6bc38109801?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxKdW5nZnJhdSUyMG1vdW50YWluJTIwdmlld3N8ZW58MXwwfHx8MTc4MzQ0MzkxNXww&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"S&B Vonlanthen"},"description":"One of the most iconic peaks in the Alps, accessible via the mountain railway from Interlaken to the Jungfraujoch station at 3454 meters. The journey itself is spectacular, and the high-altitude station offers views of Europe's longest glacier and unforgettable panoramas."},{"rank":6,"name":"Zermatt","placeId":"zermatt","regionId":"valais","regionName":"Valais","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1492119884860-63772f175a02?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxNYXR0ZXJob3JuJTIwWmVybWF0dHxlbnwxfDB8fHwxNzgzNDQ0MDM5fDA&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Chris Holgersson"},"description":"A car-free alpine village at the foot of the iconic Matterhorn, Zermatt is Switzerland's premier mountain resort with world-class hiking, skiing, and mountaineering. The dramatic Matterhorn views and charming wooden chalets make it one of Switzerland's most recognizable destinations."},{"rank":7,"name":"Matterhorn","placeId":"matterhorn","regionId":"valais","regionName":"Valais","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1586752488885-6ce47fdfd874?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxNYXR0ZXJob3JuJTIwU3dpdHplcmxhbmR8ZW58MXwwfHx8MTc4NDAyNjU5MHww&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Victor He"},"description":"Switzerland's most emblematic mountain, the Matterhorn is a globally recognized symbol of the Alps with dramatic pyramidal peaks and challenging climbing routes. Its iconic status and accessibility from Zermatt make it one of the most visited natural landmarks in the world."},{"rank":8,"name":"Bern","placeId":"bern_city","regionId":"bern","regionName":"Bern","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1620563092215-0fbc6b55cfc5?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxCZXJuJTIwU3dpdHplcmxhbmR8ZW58MXwwfHx8MTc4NDAyNjU2Mnww&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Henrique Ferreira"},"description":"Switzerland's capital city features a UNESCO World Heritage Old Town with medieval architecture, charming arcaded streets, and the famous Bear Park. Visitors are drawn to its political significance, cultural institutions, and perfectly preserved historic character."},{"rank":9,"name":"Basel","placeId":"basel_city","regionId":"basel_stadt","regionName":"Basel-Stadt","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1693643026112-d926de8c7b55?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxCYXNlbCUyMFN3aXR6ZXJsYW5kJTIwUmhpbmUlMjBjaXR5fGVufDF8MHx8fDE3ODM0NDIwODZ8MA&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Grischa"},"description":"Switzerland's second-largest city, positioned on the Rhine River where three countries meet, known for world-class museums, pharmaceutical industry, and vibrant cultural scene. Basel is a gateway to both Switzerland and the broader region with excellent transportation and cosmopolitan atmosphere."},{"rank":10,"name":"Rhine Falls","placeId":"rheinfall","regionId":"schaffhausen","regionName":"Schaffhausen","image":{"index":0,"assetPath":"","isLocal":false,"url":"https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1729506712731-9b80d00a4a0d?ixid=M3w5NTU4NjF8MHwxfHNlYXJjaHwxfHxSaGluZSUyMEZhbGxzJTIwUmhlaW5mYWxsJTIwU3dpdHplcmxhbmR8ZW58MXwwfHx8MTc4MzQ0Nzc5Mnww&ixlib=rb-4.1.0&crop=entropy&cs=tinysrgb&fit=max&fm=jpg&q=80&w=1080","credit":"Michaela Římáková"},"description":"Europe's largest waterfall by volume, located near Neuhausen with a dramatic 23-meter drop that creates a spectacular natural display year-round. Visitors can experience the falls from multiple vantage points including boat rides through the mist and viewing platforms on both Swiss and German sides."}]}